text: Greater Poland Voivodeship is one of the 16 Voivodeships of Poland. It can be found in the western part of Poland. It is mostly in the historical land Greater Poland. The capital of the Voivodeship is Poznań. It was created on 1 January 1999. ==Protected areas== Protected areas in Greater Poland Voivodeship include two National Parks and 12 Landscape Parks. These are listed below. *Drawno National Park (partly in Lubusz and West Pomeranian Voivodeships) *Greater Poland National Park *Barycz Valley Landscape Park (partly in Lower Silesian Voivodeship) *Chłapowski Landscape Park *Lednica Landscape Park *Powidz Landscape Park *Promno Landscape Park *Przemęt Landscape Park (partly in Lubusz Voivodeship) *Pszczew Landscape Park (partly in Lubusz Voivodeship) *Puszcza Zielonka Landscape Park *Rogalin Landscape Park *Sieraków Landscape Park *Warta Landscape Park *Żerków-Czeszewo Landscape Park Category:1999 establishments in Poland
title: Greater Poland Voivodeship
